items.title: HR history: Twins go deep in 7 straight innings
items.summary: The Twins made Major League history Tuesday, becoming the first team to homer in each of the first seven innings of a game in their 16-0 rout of the Padres at Target Field.

items.title: Bryant blasts Cubs out of funk with 4 RBIs
items.summary: Kris Bryant hasn't exactly scuffled, but his numbers aren't quite the same as they were last season when he won the NL MVP Award. On Tuesday night, he hit his first home run in September to spark the Cubs to an 8-3 victory over the Mets and snap a three-game losing streak.

items.title: Resurgent offense arrives on time for Cards
items.summary: A new-look Cardinals' offense greeted Cincinnati on Tuesday, and it helped the St. Louis coast to their 10th win in 12 games, keeping pace in the National League Central. They trail the Cubs by two games and hold a half-game lead over Milwaukee.
